<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E90FF1E48F75392FAF2F8E6" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="007606418E90FF1E48F75392FAF2F8E6" blockId="222.[151,1436,1178,1995]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E90FF1E48F75392FEE4FB27" bold="true" box="[199,321,1214,1239]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E90FF1E49605392FE01FB26" box="[336,420,1214,1238]" italics="true" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E498C5392FD9BFB26" box="[444,574,1214,1238]" captionStart="PLATE 64" captionStartId="223.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[166,1424,239,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-41@223.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="223" captionText="PLATE 64. Bocchus beckeri. A. Female from Malaya. Length 4.0 mm. B. Chela, holotype. Scale bar 0.23 mm for B. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278597/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plates 64A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4A655392FD20FB26" box="[597,645,1214,1238]" captionStart="PLATE 68" captionStartId="237.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,217,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-56@237.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="237" captionText="PLATE 68. A. Holotype, dorsal view. Length 3.0 mm. B, C. Chelae, holotypes. A, B. Bocchus rubricus (from Olmi 1984). C. B. rubrithorax (from Olmi 2005a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for B and 0.20 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278613/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">68A</figureCitation>
): fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4B645392FC70FB26" box="[852,981,1214,1238]" captionStart="PLATE 64" captionStartId="223.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[166,1424,239,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-41@223.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="223" captionText="PLATE 64. Bocchus beckeri. A. Female from Malaya. Length 4.0 mm. B. Chela, holotype. Scale bar 0.23 mm for B. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278597/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plates 64A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4BDC5392FBB9FB26" box="[1004,1052,1214,1238]" captionStart="PLATE 68" captionStartId="237.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,217,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-56@237.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="237" captionText="PLATE 68. A. Holotype, dorsal view. Length 3.0 mm. B, C. Chelae, holotypes. A, B. Bocchus rubricus (from Olmi 1984). C. B. rubrithorax (from Olmi 2005a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for B and 0.20 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278613/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">68A</figureCitation>
); occasionally brachypterous or micropterous or apterous; occipital carina complete; ocelli present; mandible with one, two, three or four teeth (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4890522AFF5AFAEE" box="[160,255,1286,1310]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,233,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[163,1415,270,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-69@10.[151,1436,253,1777]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="PLATE 3. A–C, F, G. Males. D, E. Mandibles. A. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. B. Fiorianteon sp. Length 3.8 mm. C. Dryinus sp. Length 3.7 mm. D. Anteon sp., Female. E. Dryinidae. F. Thaumatodryinus sp. Length 1.9 mm. G. Anteon sp. Length 2.5 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278380/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plate 3E</figureCitation>
); quadridentate mandible usually with three large teeth and one rudimentary tooth between two posterior teeth (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E48EE5206FE9BFAB2" box="[222,318,1322,1346]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,233,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[163,1415,270,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-69@10.[151,1436,253,1777]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="PLATE 3. A–C, F, G. Males. D, E. Mandibles. A. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. B. Fiorianteon sp. Length 3.8 mm. C. Dryinus sp. Length 3.7 mm. D. Anteon sp., Female. E. Dryinidae. F. Thaumatodryinus sp. Length 1.9 mm. G. Anteon sp. Length 2.5 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278380/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plate 3E</figureCitation>
); rarely quadridentate mandibles with teeth progressing larger from anterior one to posterior (as in plate 3C); palpal formula 6/3; antenna without tufts of long hairs and without rhinaria; pronotal tubercle present; epicnemium not visible, because lateral regions of prothorax continuous with mesopleura (as in plate 2G); fore wing of fully winged specimens with three cells enclosed by pigmented veins (costal, median and submedian) (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E48905296FEBFFA22" box="[160,282,1466,1490]" captionStart="PLATE 64" captionStartId="223.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[166,1424,239,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-41@223.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="223" captionText="PLATE 64. Bocchus beckeri. A. Female from Malaya. Length 4.0 mm. B. Chela, holotype. Scale bar 0.23 mm for B. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278597/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plates 64A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E49195296FEFCFA22" box="[297,345,1466,1490]" captionStart="PLATE 68" captionStartId="237.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,217,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-56@237.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="237" captionText="PLATE 68. A. Holotype, dorsal view. Length 3.0 mm. B, C. Chelae, holotypes. A, B. Bocchus rubricus (from Olmi 1984). C. B. rubrithorax (from Olmi 2005a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for B and 0.20 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278613/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">68A</figureCitation>
); fore wing with stigmal vein (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4A885296FC97FA22" box="[696,818,1466,1490]" captionStart="PLATE 64" captionStartId="223.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[166,1424,239,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-41@223.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="223" captionText="PLATE 64. Bocchus beckeri. A. Female from Malaya. Length 4.0 mm. B. Chela, holotype. Scale bar 0.23 mm for B. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278597/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plates 64A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4B705296FCD5FA22" box="[832,880,1466,1490]" captionStart="PLATE 68" captionStartId="237.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,217,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-56@237.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="237" captionText="PLATE 68. A. Holotype, dorsal view. Length 3.0 mm. B, C. Chelae, holotypes. A, B. Bocchus rubricus (from Olmi 1984). C. B. rubrithorax (from Olmi 2005a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for B and 0.20 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278613/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">68A</figureCitation>
); pterostigma of fully winged specimens present, usually very reduced (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E49A552F2FDA0FA06" box="[405,517,1502,1526]" captionStart="PLATE 64" captionStartId="223.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[166,1424,239,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-41@223.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="223" captionText="PLATE 64. Bocchus beckeri. A. Female from Malaya. Length 4.0 mm. B. Chela, holotype. Scale bar 0.23 mm for B. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278597/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plate 64A</figureCitation>
); protarsus chelate (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4AC052F2FCCEFA06" box="[752,875,1502,1526]" captionStart="PLATE 64" captionStartId="223.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[166,1424,239,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-41@223.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="223" captionText="PLATE 64. Bocchus beckeri. A. Female from Malaya. Length 4.0 mm. B. Chela, holotype. Scale bar 0.23 mm for B. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278597/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plates 64A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4B4B52F2FC0EFA06" box="[891,939,1502,1526]" captionStart="PLATE 68" captionStartId="237.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,217,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-56@237.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="237" captionText="PLATE 68. A. Holotype, dorsal view. Length 3.0 mm. B, C. Chelae, holotypes. A, B. Bocchus rubricus (from Olmi 1984). C. B. rubrithorax (from Olmi 2005a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for B and 0.20 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278613/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">68A</figureCitation>
); chela with rudimentary claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4D2B52F2FA3DFA06" box="[1307,1432,1502,1526]" captionStart="PLATE 64" captionStartId="223.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[166,1424,239,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-41@223.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="223" captionText="PLATE 64. Bocchus beckeri. A. Female from Malaya. Length 4.0 mm. B. Chela, holotype. Scale bar 0.23 mm for B. (From Olmi 1991)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278597/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plates 64B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E48A7512EFF62F9EA" box="[151,199,1538,1562]" captionStart="PLATE 65" captionStartId="224.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[222,1389,239,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-78@224.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="224" captionText="PLATE 65. A, E. Chelae, holotypes. B, C. Stigmal veins. D. Male genitalia, holotype. A. Bocchus haladai (from Olmi 2008b). B, D. B. indicus, male (from Olmi 1987a). C, E. B. laotianus, female (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.18 mm for A, 0.35 mm for B and C, 0.23 mm for D and 0.18 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278601/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">65A</figureCitation>
); protrochanter short and slightly longer than broad; tibial spurs 1/1/1, or 1/1/2. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E90FF1E4C53512FFB39F9EB" box="[1123,1180,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4C9E512EFAE8F9EA" box="[1198,1357,1538,1562]" captionStart="PLATE 67" captionStartId="228.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[197,1403,201,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-82@228.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="228" captionText="PLATE 67. A–C. Bocchus pedunculatus. D. B. reticulates. A. Dorsal view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. B. Lateral view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. C. Male genitalia of male from Malaysia. D. Holotype (from Xu et al. 2003). Scale bar 0.27 mm for C and 0.23 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278609/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plates 67A, B</figureCitation>
): fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E48CA510AFE30F9CE" box="[250,405,1574,1598]" captionStart="PLATE 67" captionStartId="228.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[197,1403,201,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-82@228.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="228" captionText="PLATE 67. A–C. Bocchus pedunculatus. D. B. reticulates. A. Dorsal view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. B. Lateral view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. C. Male genitalia of male from Malaysia. D. Holotype (from Xu et al. 2003). Scale bar 0.27 mm for C and 0.23 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278609/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plates 67A, B</figureCitation>
), rarely micropterous (only 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E90FF1E4AE1510AFBC9F9CE" authority="Ruthe" authorityName="Ruthe" authorityYear="1859" box="[721,1132,1574,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Mystrophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formicaeformis">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E90FF1E4AE1510AFBBAF9CE" box="[721,1055,1574,1598]" italics="true" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Mystrophorus formicaeformis</emphasis>
Ruthe
</taxonomicName>
, not present in the 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38E90FF1E4D70510AFF45F992" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
) or apterous (only 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E90FF1E49875167FCF3F992" authority="Ponomarenko" authorityName="Ponomarenko" authorityYear="2000" box="[439,854,1610,1635]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Mystrophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apterus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E90FF1E49875167FD0AF992" box="[439,687,1611,1635]" italics="true" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Mystrophorus apterus</emphasis>
Ponomarenko
</taxonomicName>
, not present in the 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38E90FF1E4C1C5166FB7EF992" box="[1068,1243,1610,1634]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
); occipital carina complete; mandible with one, two, three or four teeth (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4B375142FCC2F976" box="[775,871,1646,1670]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,233,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[163,1415,270,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-69@10.[151,1436,253,1777]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="PLATE 3. A–C, F, G. Males. D, E. Mandibles. A. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. B. Fiorianteon sp. Length 3.8 mm. C. Dryinus sp. Length 3.7 mm. D. Anteon sp., Female. E. Dryinidae. F. Thaumatodryinus sp. Length 1.9 mm. G. Anteon sp. Length 2.5 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278380/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plate 3E</figureCitation>
); quadridentate mandible usually with three large teeth and one rudimentary tooth between two posterior teeth (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4B7D51BEFC09F95A" box="[845,940,1682,1706]" captionStart="PLATE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,233,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[163,1415,270,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-69@10.[151,1436,253,1777]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="PLATE 3. A–C, F, G. Males. D, E. Mandibles. A. Crovettia sp. Length 2.5 mm. B. Fiorianteon sp. Length 3.8 mm. C. Dryinus sp. Length 3.7 mm. D. Anteon sp., Female. E. Dryinidae. F. Thaumatodryinus sp. Length 1.9 mm. G. Anteon sp. Length 2.5 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278380/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plate 3E</figureCitation>
); palpal formula 6/3; epicnemium invisible, because lateral regions of prothorax continuous with mesopleura (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4BA4519AFBBCF93E" box="[916,1049,1718,1742]" captionStart="PLATE 2" captionStartId="9.[151,233,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,192,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-85@9.[151,1436,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="PLATE 2. A–C, F. Females. D, E. Chelae. a, arolium; e, enlarged claw; r, rudimentary claw; s, segment 5 of protarsus. G, H. Part of mesosoma, males. a, propleuron; c, procoxa; e, epicnemium; m, mesopleuron; p, pronotum; s, scutum; t, tegula. A. Aphelopus sp. B, E, H. Dryinus sp. C. Gonatopus sp. D. Anteon sp. F. Conganteon sp. G.Bocchus sp. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278378/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plate 2G, H</figureCitation>
); in fully winged specimens fore wing with three cells enclosed by pigmented veins (costal, median and submedian) (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4C7851F6FB7CF902" box="[1096,1241,1754,1778]" captionStart="PLATE 67" captionStartId="228.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[197,1403,201,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-82@228.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="228" captionText="PLATE 67. A–C. Bocchus pedunculatus. D. B. reticulates. A. Dorsal view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. B. Lateral view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. C. Male genitalia of male from Malaysia. D. Holotype (from Xu et al. 2003). Scale bar 0.27 mm for C and 0.23 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278609/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plate 67A, B</figureCitation>
); in fully winged specimens fore wing with stigmal vein (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4A6851D2FD4DF8E6" box="[600,744,1790,1814]" captionStart="PLATE 67" captionStartId="228.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[197,1403,201,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-82@228.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="228" captionText="PLATE 67. A–C. Bocchus pedunculatus. D. B. reticulates. A. Dorsal view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. B. Lateral view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. C. Male genitalia of male from Malaysia. D. Holotype (from Xu et al. 2003). Scale bar 0.27 mm for C and 0.23 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278609/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plate 67A, B</figureCitation>
); pterostigma present (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E90FF1E4BDC51D2FBD8F8E6" box="[1004,1149,1790,1814]" captionStart="PLATE 67" captionStartId="228.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[197,1403,201,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-82@228.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="228" captionText="PLATE 67. A–C. Bocchus pedunculatus. D. B. reticulates. A. Dorsal view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. B. Lateral view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. C. Male genitalia of male from Malaysia. D. Holotype (from Xu et al. 2003). Scale bar 0.27 mm for C and 0.23 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278609/files/figure.png" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Plate 67A, B</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E90FF1E48F7500EFE4EF8CA" box="[199,491,1826,1851]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="007606418E90FF1E48F7500EFE4EF8CA" blockId="222.[151,1436,1178,1995]" box="[199,491,1826,1851]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E90FF1E48F7500EFEC5F8CB" bold="true" box="[199,352,1826,1851]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Distribution.</emphasis>
Worldwide.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E90FF1E48F7506BFC53F83A" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="007606418E90FF1E48F7506BFDCBF872" blockId="222.[151,1436,1178,1995]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E90FF1E48F7506BFEB4F8AF" bold="true" box="[199,273,1863,1887]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Hosts.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E90FF1E4912506AFE0BF8AE" box="[290,430,1862,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Caliscelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Caliscelidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E90FF1E49F2506AFDC2F8AE" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1866" box="[450,615,1862,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Tropiduchidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tropiduchidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E90FF1E4A4C506AFCADF8AE" baseAuthorityName="Guglielmino &amp; Olmi" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[636,776,1862,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cicadellidae</taxonomicName>
(except 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E90FF1E4B4C506AFC58F8AE" baseAuthorityName="Guglielmino &amp; Olmi" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[892,1021,1862,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Idiocerinae">Idiocerinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E90FF1E4C22506AFB07F8AE" baseAuthorityName="Guglielmino &amp; Olmi" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1042,1186,1862,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Macropsinae">Macropsinae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E90FF1E4CDD506AFA30F8AE" baseAuthorityName="Guglielmino &amp; Olmi" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[1261,1429,1862,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Typhlocybinae">Typhlocybinae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08E90FF1E48AE5046FE76F872" author="Guglielmino &amp; Olmi" box="[158,467,1898,1922]" firstAuthor="Guglielmino" pageId="222" pageNumber="223" pagination="165 - 298" refId="ref360036" refString="Guglielmino, A. &amp; Olmi, M. (1997) A host-parasite catalog of world Dryinidae (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea). Contributions on Entomology, International, 2 (2), 165 - 298." type="journal article" year="1997">Guglielmino &amp; Olmi, 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 2006, 2007).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E90FF1E48F750A3FB04F856" blockId="222.[151,1436,1178,1995]" box="[199,1185,1934,1959]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E90FF1E48F750A3FED1F857" bold="true" box="[199,372,1934,1959]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">World species.</emphasis>
One hundred and four species are known, sixteen in the 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38E90FF1E4BDF50A2FB38F856" box="[1007,1181,1934,1958]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E90FF1E48F7509FFC53F83A" blockId="222.[151,1436,1178,1995]" box="[199,1014,1970,1995]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E90FF1E48F7509FFED7F83B" bold="true" box="[199,370,1971,1995]" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">World genera.</emphasis>
Three genera are known, only one in the 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38E90FF1E4B75509EFC57F83A" box="[837,1010,1970,1994]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="222" pageNumber="223">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="54B656C98E91FF1F48A75051FEB6F842" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278597" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5278597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278597/files/figure.png" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" startId="223.[151,233,1917,1940]" targetBox="[166,1424,239,1859]" targetPageId="223">
<paragraph id="007606418E91FF1F48A75051FEB6F842" blockId="223.[151,1436,1917,1970]" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E91FF1F48A75051FEB4F864" bold="true" box="[151,273,1917,1940]" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">PLATE 64.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E91FF1F49285052FE65F864" box="[280,448,1918,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Bocchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beckeri">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E91FF1F49285052FE65F864" box="[280,448,1918,1940]" italics="true" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">Bocchus beckeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
